CHINA unveils new main battle tank model - potential technological advancement in PLA ground forces' armored capabilities (China Daily)
KREMLIN signals openness to CUBA dialogue amid US sanctions - seeks diplomatic engagement on Caribbean tensions (TASS)
BANGLADESH holds national election amid political tensions - opposition claims voter suppression, low turnout reported after years of HASINA government crackdowns (BBC)
AFGHANISTAN: TALIBAN claims downing U.S. military jet in combat zone - PENTAGON immediately denies report as false; no confirmation of aircraft loss (Xinhua)
RUSSIA warns against WESTERN destabilization attempts in BELARUS: Diplomat signals close security cooperation between MOSCOW and MINSK amid rising geopolitical tensions (TASS)
GLOBAL POWERS: EU, AFRICAN UNION, UN condemn child soldier recruitment - joint statement marks International Day against use of minors in armed conflict (UN)
SWEDEN begins first NATO air policing mission over ICELAND, marking expanded alliance commitment after recent membership - defense signals shift in Nordic security posture (Janes)
TEXAS airspace disrupted: US MILITARY conducts laser tests, reports of CARTEL surveillance drones near border create operational uncertainty (AP)
RUSSIA maintains stance on NEW START nuclear treaty — no changes to Feb 4 Foreign Ministry position on treaty's future (TASS)
RUSSIA diplomat RYABKOV claims US economic influence declining, dollar's global dominance eroding amid shifting geopolitical landscape (TASS)
SAUDI ARABIA's SAMI unveils new Heet tactical vehicles at World Defense Show 2026 - indigenous military platform design (Janes)
BREAKING: US MILITARY conducts airstrikes against ISIS targets in NIGERIA - precision strike targeting militant positions in ongoing counterterrorism operation (AP)
RUSSIA: 5 states quitting OTTAWA CONVENTION signals potential arms control breakdown — could impact European security landscape (TASS)
RUSSIA diplomat RYABKOV suggests UKRAINE peace talks must follow ANCHORAGE framework - signals potential diplomatic opening amid ongoing conflict (TASS)
RUSSIA accuses US of blocking CUBA flights, disrupting tourism: Foreign Ministry spokesperson ZAKHAROVA blames "external forces" for ongoing travel restrictions (TASS)
RUSSIA signals openness to US dialogue on UKRAINE conflict: Deputy Foreign Minister RYABKOV says ready for "equal terms" negotiations amid ongoing tensions (TASS)
RUSSIA unveils S180 military drone with advanced evasion capabilities against FPV attack drones - claims high-speed maneuverability prevents interception (TASS)
US approves $142B arms package to SAUDI ARABIA — largest single defense sale in bilateral history, includes advanced fighter jets, missile systems, precision munitions (Reuters)
SUDAN conflict: New peace proposal emerges amid ongoing fighting between ARMY and RAPID SUPPORT FORCES - potential diplomatic breakthrough uncertain (AllAfrica)
BANGLADESH holds national election amid opposition boycott - AWAMI LEAGUE seeks 4th consecutive term, low voter turnout reported in early hours (Al Jazeera)
UKRAINE athlete HERASKEVYCH banned from OLYMPICS after wearing memorial helmet highlighting war casualties - IOC rules against athlete's protest of RUSSIA invasion (Al Jazeera)
BANGLADESH polls close after contentious election - opposition claims voter suppression, ruling AWAMI LEAGUE seeks 4th consecutive term amid protests, low turnout (Al Jazeera)
RUSSIA economy faces critical strain: Defense production vs. agricultural output creating major resource allocation tensions in ongoing UKRAINE war effort (RFE/RL)
RUSSIA hopes for OLYMPIC reinstatement after 70+ international sports federations clear Russian athletes for competition — Foreign Ministry spokesperson (TASS)
LEGAL FILING: Attorneys seek CIA, NSA documents on JEFFREY EPSTEIN's potential intelligence connections - court motion demands full disclosure of classified files (Anadolu Agency)
RUSSIA claims UKRAINE attempted assassination of Russian official, alleges deliberate effort to block peace negotiations - ZELENSKY linked to "coordinated" operation on RUSSIAN territory (TASS)
RUSSIA's PUTIN thanks UAE president for assistance in capturing suspect linked to alleged assassination attempt against military leadership (Anadolu Agency)
AUSTRALIA: Terrorist attack at BONDI BEACH targets Jewish event - multiple casualties reported, suspect neutralized by police. Active investigation underway in SYDNEY (Time)
U.S. CENTCOM conducts airstrikes against ISIS targets in SYRIA - precision strikes targeting militant infrastructure, ongoing counter-terrorism operation (CENTCOM)
